headline: Home-Goods Stocks Slide on Tariff Plans
summary: Shares of furniture and other home-goods retailers slipped Monday, after President Trump announced new tariffs Friday on kitchen cabinets, upholstered furniture and bathroom vanities. Shares of Williams-Sonoma dropped 4.

headline: Trump says details coming on furniture tariffs
summary: WASHINGTON (Reuters) -U.S. President Donald Trump on Monday said details were forthcoming on tariffs for furniture imports, after announcing levies of up to 50% on such goods last week.  Trump announced a 50% tariff on imported kitchen cabinets and vanities, along with a 30% levy on upholstered furniture, which are set to take effect on October 1.
